  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A fencing walk takes an hour per kilometre at a slow inspection pace. Walk every field boundary and internal division fence three times a year; twice a year is the realistic minimum on a busy holding. Keep a notepad and mark problems as you find them so you can return with the right materials."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Late winter walk (February to March)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The winter walk catches frost damage and debris accumulation before the spring season begins. Check:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Post heave, frost lifts timber posts if the ground freezes to depth. Any post that has risen should be re-driven back to the correct depth and compacted."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Wire tension, wire contracts in cold weather and loosens when it warms. Re-tension any wire that has noticeably drooped."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ""
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Fence staples",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                        "attrs": {
                          "termSlug": "fence-staple"
                        }
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ", tap back any that have worked loose. Loose staples are a leg-injury risk."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Storm debris, branches lying on or against the fence. Remove these before livestock are turned out onto the new season's grass."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summer walk (June to July)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The summer walk catches damage from animal pressure through the grazing season. Check:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Rubbing posts, cattle and pigs rub against timber posts and can work them loose. A post that rocks needs re-driving or replacing."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Electric fencing, check voltage with a tester. The "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "electric fence troubleshooting",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "techniqueLink",
                        "attrs": {
                          "techniqueSlug": "electric-fence-troubleshooting",
                          "label": "electric fence troubleshooting"
                        }
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " tutorial covers fault-finding for voltage loss."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Gate hinges and latches, the most common cause of escape."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Autumn walk (October to November)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Check the boundary fences before livestock are moved in from summer grazing to winter quarters. Any "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "stock-proof",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "stock-proof"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " deficiencies in a field about to receive a wintering group should be repaired before they go in, not after they've used the weak point to explore the neighbours' field."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "infoPanel",
        "attrs": {
          "tone": "info"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Keep a stock of repair materials: a few spare timber posts, a roll of stock fencing, a coil of barbed wire, a bag of fence staples, and a reel of polywire for temporary repairs. An escape at 6 p.m. on a Saturday is much easier to manage if you can fix the breach temporarily on the spot."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Electric fencing maintenance"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Electric fence maintenance is covered in the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "setting up electric fencing",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "techniqueLink",
                "attrs": {
                  "techniqueSlug": "setting-up-electric-fencing-on-a-smallholding",
                  "label": "setting up electric fencing"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "electric fence troubleshooting",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "techniqueLink",
                "attrs": {
                  "techniqueSlug": "electric-fence-troubleshooting",
                  "label": "electric fence troubleshooting"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " tutorials. At each walk, check that the earth stake is fully driven, connections are clean, and any plants touching the wire are cleared."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}